WEBVTT

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:03.704
♪

00:00:03.704 --> 00:00:05.305
Ray it's me, Ray!

00:00:05.305 --> 00:00:07.608
(Ray)
Yuma you gotta
hurry, please!

00:00:07.608 --> 00:00:09.276
<i>(screaming)</i>

00:00:09.276 --> 00:00:11.912
You there?

00:00:11.912 --> 00:00:13.514
Hold on, Ray!

00:00:13.514 --> 00:00:17.184
♪

00:00:17.184 --> 00:00:18.452
Oh no!

00:00:18.452 --> 00:00:21.054
♪

00:00:21.054 --> 00:00:23.390
Ray!

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:25.459
Reporting for duty, Yuma?

00:00:25.459 --> 00:00:26.860
Yeah, sure.

00:00:26.860 --> 00:00:29.463
But who's... that?

00:00:29.463 --> 00:00:31.965
An unwelcome intrusion.

00:00:31.965 --> 00:00:34.268
We'll finish this later.

00:00:35.869 --> 00:00:37.271
Vector!

00:00:37.271 --> 00:00:43.343
♪

00:00:43.343 --> 00:00:44.511
Ray!

00:00:44.511 --> 00:00:47.381
Oh no, are you okay?

00:00:47.381 --> 00:00:48.582
Yeah.

00:00:48.582 --> 00:00:51.018
Who was that guy?

00:00:51.018 --> 00:00:53.620
He's the worst
Barian of them all.

00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:56.156
And we've been
after him for years.

00:00:56.156 --> 00:00:57.925
Vector.

00:00:57.925 --> 00:00:59.993
Vector?

00:00:59.993 --> 00:01:03.697
Listen, Yuma,
I've gotta go after him.

00:01:03.697 --> 00:01:05.232
But while I'm away,

00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:08.101
it is your duty to
protect this world.

00:01:08.101 --> 00:01:10.637
Sir, you can
count on me!

00:01:10.637 --> 00:01:12.673
♪

00:01:12.673 --> 00:01:14.942
(Ray)
I'm leaving
these with you.

00:01:14.942 --> 00:01:16.510
-Why?
-Because you're gonna need

00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:19.413
all the help
you can get, Yuma.

00:01:19.413 --> 00:01:24.451
Maybe so but these are
Barian cards, Ray.

00:01:24.451 --> 00:01:27.120
And I think you already
know you have to keep it

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:30.257
a total secret that
I gave these cards to you.

00:01:30.257 --> 00:01:33.493
Yeah, but...
maybe...

00:01:33.493 --> 00:01:35.395
maybe we should
tell Astral that

00:01:35.395 --> 00:01:36.797
even though
you're a Barian,

00:01:36.797 --> 00:01:37.764
you're one of
the good guys.

00:01:37.764 --> 00:01:39.099
We can't.

00:01:39.099 --> 00:01:41.635
If anybody found
out about me now

00:01:41.635 --> 00:01:45.839
that intel would only put
Astral in extreme danger.

00:01:45.839 --> 00:01:46.873
But when can...

00:01:46.873 --> 00:01:48.141
(Ray)
Astral will know everything

00:01:48.141 --> 00:01:50.644
about me soon,
I promise.

00:01:50.644 --> 00:01:54.615
But until then, you'll
have to trust me.

00:01:54.615 --> 00:01:56.216
You have my
complete trust.

00:01:56.216 --> 00:01:57.618
I'm at your command!

00:01:57.618 --> 00:01:59.886
I'm counting
on you, Yuma.

00:01:59.886 --> 00:02:07.561
♪

00:02:07.995 --> 00:02:13.400
♪

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:14.935
♪ Still together as one ♪

00:02:14.935 --> 00:02:16.536
♪ 'Cause divided we're none ♪

00:02:16.536 --> 00:02:18.839
♪ Ready to go
we feel the flow ♪

00:02:18.839 --> 00:02:21.842
♪ So don't stand in our way
you know we ain't afraid ♪

00:02:21.842 --> 00:02:24.311
♪ This is our time,
we're in control ♪

00:02:24.311 --> 00:02:27.247
♪ If I trip up today
you just wipe it away ♪

00:02:27.247 --> 00:02:29.583
♪ All of my fears
are gone, erased ♪

00:02:29.583 --> 00:02:32.519
♪ Let us tear down the walls
'til the final night falls ♪

00:02:32.519 --> 00:02:35.255
♪ The bonds of our souls
can't be replaced ♪

00:02:35.255 --> 00:02:36.957
♪ Let us fight together ♪

00:02:36.957 --> 00:02:40.293
♪ Regret it never,
our dreams will be ♪

00:02:40.293 --> 00:02:42.963
♪ Halfway to forever ♪

00:02:42.963 --> 00:02:45.666
♪ Our light comes
shining through ♪

00:02:45.666 --> 00:02:48.268
♪ Reach down deep,
beat defeat ♪

00:02:48.268 --> 00:02:50.937
♪ Do all that we can do ♪

00:02:50.937 --> 00:02:53.607
♪ Halfway to forever ♪

00:02:53.607 --> 00:02:56.276
♪ We've got
nothing to lose ♪

00:02:56.276 --> 00:02:58.945
♪ Keep breathing,
believing ♪

00:02:58.945 --> 00:03:04.217
♪ Halfway to forever ♪♪

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:10.724
♪

00:03:10.724 --> 00:03:12.492
(Mizar)
Yuma Tsukumo
and Astral

00:03:12.492 --> 00:03:15.662
defeated Alito and Girag
in the human world.

00:03:15.662 --> 00:03:19.066
They still have not fully
recovered from their duels.

00:03:19.066 --> 00:03:24.738
Mizar, now you and I will
have to settle this score.

00:03:24.738 --> 00:03:27.674
(Vector)
What's the matter
Girag? Alito?

00:03:27.674 --> 00:03:30.844
You look a little...
under the weather.

00:03:30.844 --> 00:03:33.246
♪

00:03:33.246 --> 00:03:37.617
Well, the doctor
will see you now!

00:03:37.617 --> 00:03:40.554
It is... Vector.

00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:43.056
♪

00:03:43.056 --> 00:03:45.425
Pardon me,
what did you say?

00:03:45.425 --> 00:03:46.693
"We are weak.

00:03:46.693 --> 00:03:49.563
We do not have the
strength to beat them."

00:03:49.563 --> 00:03:53.100
"Can you cure us?"

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:57.003
Sorry... but I'm just
a veterinarian!

00:03:57.003 --> 00:04:02.209
♪

00:04:02.209 --> 00:04:04.511
Stop it, Mizar.

00:04:04.511 --> 00:04:06.847
♪

00:04:06.847 --> 00:04:09.282
This is no time to be
fighting each other.

00:04:09.282 --> 00:04:13.253
-Well, that time is coming.
-Anytime, Mizar.

00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:15.455
Nice of you
to show up, Vector.

00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:17.524
You have missed a lot.

00:04:17.524 --> 00:04:20.527
Unfortunately,
Yuma and Astral

00:04:20.527 --> 00:04:22.662
managed to stop
your brilliant plan

00:04:22.662 --> 00:04:26.900
to have Dr. Faker and Vetrix
destroy Astral World.

00:04:26.900 --> 00:04:30.470
♪

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.372
But you were
off somewhere,

00:04:32.372 --> 00:04:35.475
not taking responsibility
for your failure.

00:04:35.475 --> 00:04:36.843
But I didn't fail.

00:04:36.843 --> 00:04:40.614
I was there and this was
all part of my plan.

00:04:40.614 --> 00:04:45.085
Yuma, Astral,
Kite, Shark...

00:04:45.085 --> 00:04:49.022
they're all about to meet
their fate together!

00:04:49.022 --> 00:04:52.492
I know exactly
what I'm doing.

00:04:52.492 --> 00:04:56.897
Trust in me and soon
I will crush them!

00:04:56.897 --> 00:04:58.698
No one is going
to listen to you!

00:04:58.698 --> 00:05:00.133
That is enough.

00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:01.701
I am warning you, Vector.

00:05:01.701 --> 00:05:03.436
No more of your
secret stunts.

00:05:03.436 --> 00:05:05.238
Or you will
answer to me.

00:05:05.238 --> 00:05:07.307
♪

00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.675
Come!

00:05:08.675 --> 00:05:11.611
It's time to
begin the end!

00:05:11.611 --> 00:05:17.150
♪

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:20.420
With Utopia Ray V and these
Barian cards Ray gave me,

00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:22.956
I'm invincible!

00:05:22.956 --> 00:05:25.225
Not even the Barians
can beat me now!

00:05:25.225 --> 00:05:27.360
What are you
so excited about?

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:28.361
Excited?...

00:05:28.361 --> 00:05:30.764
You're hiding
something from us.

00:05:30.764 --> 00:05:32.666
It's obvious, Yuma.

00:05:32.666 --> 00:05:35.168
You might as well
face it, Yuma.

00:05:35.168 --> 00:05:38.572
You can't keep a secret!

00:05:39.940 --> 00:05:42.609
♪

00:05:42.609 --> 00:05:45.445
(Bronk)
All right,
where are ya?

00:05:45.445 --> 00:05:48.515
Show your cowardly faces
you Barian babies!

00:05:48.515 --> 00:05:51.184
Crawl out of
your little holes!

00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:53.019
Are you men or mice?

00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:55.288
Uh guys, I'm not sure
it's such a good idea

00:05:55.288 --> 00:05:57.324
to get the Barians mad at me.

00:05:57.324 --> 00:05:59.759
Oh, Yuma, they're just
trying to help you out.

00:05:59.759 --> 00:06:01.828
I wish they'd butt out!

00:06:01.828 --> 00:06:03.797
Guys, what's that?

00:06:05.999 --> 00:06:08.001
Guys, what's that?

00:06:08.001 --> 00:06:11.304
♪

00:06:11.304 --> 00:06:13.440
Whatever it is,
it's not good.

00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:25.785
♪

00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:32.158
Guys, is everybody okay?

00:06:32.158 --> 00:06:34.294
-Uh-huh.
-Oh, yeah, just great.

00:06:36.763 --> 00:06:38.164
Yuma, what is happening?

00:06:38.164 --> 00:06:40.367
It's gotta be
the Barians.

00:06:40.367 --> 00:06:44.871
♪

00:06:44.871 --> 00:06:46.306
Who are you?

00:06:46.306 --> 00:06:49.276
I am what you dread.

00:06:49.276 --> 00:06:53.580
My name is Vector.

00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:56.349
I know that guy.

00:06:56.349 --> 00:06:59.219
(Ray)
He's the worst Barian
of them all.

00:06:59.219 --> 00:07:02.322
And we've been
after him for years.

00:07:02.322 --> 00:07:04.124
Vector.

00:07:04.124 --> 00:07:06.826
Yuma Tsukumo, Astral.

00:07:06.826 --> 00:07:10.730
I've come here to destroy
you and your world.

00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:13.199
-Astral what do we...
-Quickly, Yuma, the others.

00:07:13.199 --> 00:07:15.602
Gotcha!
Go, guys, run!

00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:18.171
♪

00:07:18.171 --> 00:07:21.775
I activate a Barian
Sphere Field!

00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:33.253
♪

00:07:33.253 --> 00:07:34.354
Yuma!

00:07:34.354 --> 00:07:39.893
♪

00:07:39.893 --> 00:07:42.996
It's been a while
since we dueled, Yuma.

00:07:42.996 --> 00:07:44.631
What're you
talking about?

00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:46.299
I never dueled
you in my life!

00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:49.002
How quickly
we forget.

00:07:49.002 --> 00:07:53.640
We had lots of fun together
when I took over Dr. Faker.

00:07:53.640 --> 00:07:55.909
♪

00:07:55.909 --> 00:07:57.143
What?

00:07:57.143 --> 00:07:59.512
You were the one who was
controlling Dr. Faker?

00:07:59.512 --> 00:08:01.614
I remember that Barian.

00:08:01.614 --> 00:08:05.285
That was just a preview.

00:08:05.285 --> 00:08:09.222
I've come to destroy
and to crush you!

00:08:09.222 --> 00:08:11.658
And not just
Astral World.

00:08:11.658 --> 00:08:13.693
The human world too!

00:08:13.693 --> 00:08:15.595
He means it, Yuma.

00:08:15.595 --> 00:08:16.930
I've heard enough!

00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:19.733
This ends right
here, right now!

00:08:19.733 --> 00:08:21.534
Duel Disk go!

00:08:21.534 --> 00:08:26.573
♪

00:08:26.573 --> 00:08:29.109
Duel Gazer, let's roll!

00:08:29.109 --> 00:08:31.678
♪

00:08:31.678 --> 00:08:36.516
You should both prepare
for some shocks.

00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:38.118
-Let's duel!
-Let's duel!

00:08:38.118 --> 00:08:40.253
I'll go first.

00:08:40.253 --> 00:08:43.456
♪

00:08:43.456 --> 00:08:45.992
I summon
Umbral Horror Ghoul!

00:08:45.992 --> 00:08:52.699
♪

00:08:52.699 --> 00:08:56.169
I activate Umbral Horror
Ghoul's special ability.

00:08:56.169 --> 00:08:59.873
By lowering Umbral Horror
Ghoul's attack points to zero,

00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:02.776
I can summon an Umbral
monster from my hand

00:09:02.776 --> 00:09:04.911
with zero attack points.

00:09:04.911 --> 00:09:08.515
Appear, Umbral
Horror Unform!

00:09:08.515 --> 00:09:10.083
Now get ready, Yuma.

00:09:10.083 --> 00:09:13.286
I overlay Level 4
Umbral Horror Ghoul

00:09:13.286 --> 00:09:15.922
and Umbral
Horror Unform!

00:09:15.922 --> 00:09:19.759
With these two monsters,
I build the Overlay Network!

00:09:19.759 --> 00:09:24.564
I Xyz Summon Number 66:
Master Key Beetle!

00:09:24.564 --> 00:09:41.047
♪

00:09:41.047 --> 00:09:43.950
He's already played
a Number Card, Astral!

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:46.319
This does not
bode well for us.

00:09:46.319 --> 00:09:49.255
And now, I activate
the spell...

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:52.792
Magical Tomb!

00:09:52.792 --> 00:09:54.994
I select one card
in your deck

00:09:54.994 --> 00:09:58.364
and put it inside
the Magical Tomb!

00:09:58.364 --> 00:10:01.000
What?

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:05.772
Yuma Tsukumo, I happen to know
that you have a Barian card.

00:10:05.772 --> 00:10:08.475
♪

00:10:08.475 --> 00:10:12.946
So I'm sealing away your
Limited Barian's Force!

00:10:12.946 --> 00:10:28.828
♪

00:10:28.828 --> 00:10:31.064
You can no longer
rank up your monsters.

00:10:31.064 --> 00:10:33.233
So I can't use
Utopia Ray V.

00:10:33.233 --> 00:10:37.737
Next, I activate Master Key
Beetle's special ability!

00:10:37.737 --> 00:10:41.107
By using one Overlay Unit,
I choose one card,

00:10:41.107 --> 00:10:44.878
and you can't destroy it,
no matter what!

00:10:44.878 --> 00:10:47.347
♪

00:10:47.347 --> 00:10:51.784
I choose
Magical Tomb!

00:10:51.784 --> 00:10:55.255
Now Limited Barian's Force
is totally untouchable, Astral!

00:10:55.255 --> 00:10:59.859
It seems that is the card
Vector fears the most.

00:10:59.859 --> 00:11:04.264
I place one card facedown
and end my turn.

00:11:04.264 --> 00:11:05.798
That was easy.

00:11:05.798 --> 00:11:07.867
Without Limited
Barian's Force,

00:11:07.867 --> 00:11:09.969
you can't win!

00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:12.205
Yuma.

00:11:12.205 --> 00:11:13.646
♪

00:11:17.210 --> 00:11:18.678
Go ahead, Yuma.

00:11:18.678 --> 00:11:21.114
Draw if you dare.

00:11:21.114 --> 00:11:25.118
Oh, I dare!

00:11:25.118 --> 00:11:27.987
I summon
Gagaga Magician!

00:11:27.987 --> 00:11:32.959
♪

00:11:32.959 --> 00:11:36.596
Next I activate the
spell card Gagagawind.

00:11:36.596 --> 00:11:40.200
I can summon Gagaga Girl
with one extra Level!

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:43.836
♪

00:11:43.836 --> 00:11:45.104
Yuma's starting strong!

00:11:45.104 --> 00:11:46.372
Like a wildcat.

00:11:46.372 --> 00:11:48.575
Yay! Go Yuma!

00:11:48.575 --> 00:11:54.280
Now I overlay Level 4 Gagaga
Magician and Gagaga Girl!

00:11:54.280 --> 00:11:57.383
With these two monsters,
I build the Overlay Network!

00:11:57.383 --> 00:12:01.754
I Xyz Summon
Number 39: Utopia!

00:12:01.754 --> 00:12:09.696
♪

00:12:09.696 --> 00:12:13.866
Utopia's useless without
Limited Barian's Force.

00:12:13.866 --> 00:12:16.903
Without its magic,
you need a miracle!

00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:20.106
Yuma, activate Gagaga Girl's
special ability.

00:12:20.106 --> 00:12:23.409
Right! When Gagaga Girl
is used to Xyz Summon,

00:12:23.409 --> 00:12:25.745
its special
ability activates!

00:12:25.745 --> 00:12:28.414
Your monster's attack
points disappear!

00:12:28.414 --> 00:12:31.417
Cell Phone Subtraction!

00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:34.520
What? Master Key Beetle's
attack points gone?

00:12:34.520 --> 00:12:36.155
Go, Utopia!

00:12:36.155 --> 00:12:41.361
Destroy Master Key Beetle
with Rising Sun Slash!

00:12:41.361 --> 00:12:51.437
♪

00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:55.508
I activate Master Key
Beetle's special ability.

00:12:55.508 --> 00:12:58.144
Now I can keep Master
Key Beetle around

00:12:58.144 --> 00:13:01.014
by destroying Magical Tomb!

00:13:01.014 --> 00:13:07.987
♪

00:13:07.987 --> 00:13:11.991
Master Key Beetle arise!

00:13:11.991 --> 00:13:15.461
♪

00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:18.131
The card that was sealed
away returns to your hand

00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:19.899
at the end
of this turn.

00:13:19.899 --> 00:13:20.967
Tough break.

00:13:20.967 --> 00:13:23.202
Your plan's not
working out, Vector.

00:13:23.202 --> 00:13:25.872
(Astral)
Why would Vector go to
so much trouble to secure

00:13:25.872 --> 00:13:29.409
Limited Barian's Force only
to let us have it back?

00:13:29.409 --> 00:13:32.745
I activate the trap
Corrupted Keys!

00:13:32.745 --> 00:13:37.050
It summons three Umbral
Horror Mirage Tokens!

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:42.922
♪

00:13:42.922 --> 00:13:46.726
-Whoa, that's not good.
-No, it is not.

00:13:46.726 --> 00:13:49.562
(Vector)
These Tokens have the same
number of attack points

00:13:49.562 --> 00:13:51.698
as Master Key Beetle!

00:13:51.698 --> 00:13:54.334
♪

00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:56.536
They don't have any
attack points, Astral!

00:13:56.536 --> 00:13:58.738
Vector is not a fool.

00:13:58.738 --> 00:14:02.008
This must serve some
secret purpose.

00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:03.309
Guess we'll see.

00:14:03.309 --> 00:14:05.011
I end my turn!

00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:09.115
Now Limited Barian's
Force returns to my hand!

00:14:09.115 --> 00:14:11.651
As long as I have this,
we're good to go!

00:14:11.651 --> 00:14:13.753
Remain on guard, Yuma.

00:14:13.753 --> 00:14:16.322
♪

00:14:16.322 --> 00:14:19.459
Time to get serious!

00:14:19.459 --> 00:14:21.661
I draw!

00:14:21.661 --> 00:14:26.999
I activate the spell card
Umbral Horror Refresh!

00:14:26.999 --> 00:14:30.336
My monster's attack
points return to normal.

00:14:30.336 --> 00:14:36.376
So Master Key Beetle's 2500
attack points are restored!

00:14:36.376 --> 00:14:40.346
Now I regain the same
number of life points!

00:14:40.346 --> 00:14:42.315
♪

00:14:42.315 --> 00:14:44.083
And my three
Mirage Tokens

00:14:44.083 --> 00:14:48.388
each get a 2500 attack
point increase as well.

00:14:50.223 --> 00:14:53.359
He's got four monsters
with 2500 attack points!

00:14:53.359 --> 00:14:55.261
♪

00:14:55.261 --> 00:14:59.632
Mirage Tokens, swarm
all over Utopia!

00:14:59.632 --> 00:15:02.368
♪

00:15:02.368 --> 00:15:06.139
(Yuma)
Utopia's got 2500 attack
points, same as them.

00:15:06.139 --> 00:15:08.808
But a Number can only be
destroyed by another Number,

00:15:08.808 --> 00:15:10.576
so Utopia's safe!

00:15:10.576 --> 00:15:13.012
Yuma, you must stop
this attack at once!

00:15:13.012 --> 00:15:14.113
Why?

00:15:14.113 --> 00:15:16.616
Vector would not
attack without reason.

00:15:16.616 --> 00:15:18.384
You're right, Astral.

00:15:18.384 --> 00:15:24.056
I use two Overlay Units to put
a stop to your Tokens attacks!

00:15:24.056 --> 00:15:26.025
Light Wing Shield!

00:15:26.025 --> 00:15:29.262
♪

00:15:29.262 --> 00:15:32.799
Umbral Mirage Token
Number 3... attack!

00:15:32.799 --> 00:15:34.066
I don't get it.

00:15:34.066 --> 00:15:36.035
What's he got
up his sleeve?

00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:37.670
Hmm.

00:15:37.670 --> 00:15:40.440
(Vector)
Attack Utopia!

00:15:40.440 --> 00:15:45.378
♪

00:15:45.378 --> 00:15:49.649
I activate the spell
Umbral Horror Retaliation!

00:15:49.649 --> 00:15:51.851
♪

00:15:51.851 --> 00:15:54.654
Since you destroyed my
Umbral Horror monster,

00:15:54.654 --> 00:15:57.623
this card destroys
your monster!

00:15:57.623 --> 00:16:00.326
Vanish, Utopia!

00:16:00.326 --> 00:16:01.694
This can't be!

00:16:01.694 --> 00:16:06.899
♪

00:16:06.899 --> 00:16:08.935
Utopia!

00:16:11.037 --> 00:16:13.072
Utopia!

00:16:13.072 --> 00:16:16.142
Save your screams for
there is more to come!

00:16:16.142 --> 00:16:18.711
Master Key Beetle attack!

00:16:18.711 --> 00:16:20.446
Key Blast!

00:16:20.446 --> 00:16:26.352
♪

00:16:26.352 --> 00:16:29.889
A good time
to end my turn.

00:16:29.889 --> 00:16:32.825
Vector still has three
monsters on his field.

00:16:32.825 --> 00:16:36.629
We are at
a disadvantage.

00:16:36.629 --> 00:16:38.498
Yeah, and
without Utopia,

00:16:38.498 --> 00:16:40.500
I can't bring
out Utopia Ray V.

00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:41.868
(Ray)
Yuma!

00:16:41.868 --> 00:16:44.871
♪

00:16:44.871 --> 00:16:47.306
Look, it's Ray!

00:16:47.306 --> 00:16:49.175
Ray.

00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.043
You.

00:16:51.043 --> 00:16:52.311
Yuma, listen.

00:16:52.311 --> 00:16:54.046
You can wipe him out!

00:16:54.046 --> 00:16:59.218
Just remember... use
your secret weapons!

00:16:59.218 --> 00:17:00.286
(Yuma)
That's right.

00:17:00.286 --> 00:17:02.655
Those Barian
cards he gave me!

00:17:02.655 --> 00:17:07.260
♪

00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:10.229
What secret weapons?

00:17:10.229 --> 00:17:13.399
Oh, yeah!

00:17:13.399 --> 00:17:15.201
It's my turn!

00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:23.543
♪

00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.579
It's in the bag, Astral!

00:17:26.579 --> 00:17:28.381
Vector!

00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:32.485
I summon V Salamander!

00:17:32.485 --> 00:17:34.820
♪

00:17:34.820 --> 00:17:37.189
And that's bad
news for you!

00:17:37.189 --> 00:17:39.225
V Salamander
also lets me get

00:17:39.225 --> 00:17:41.694
Utopia back
from my graveyard!

00:17:41.694 --> 00:17:45.464
What? A card that
resurrects Utopia?

00:17:45.464 --> 00:17:46.499
(Yuma)
That's right!

00:17:46.499 --> 00:17:48.634
So look who's coming back!

00:17:48.634 --> 00:17:53.105
♪

00:17:53.105 --> 00:17:58.511
I activate Rank-Up-Magic
Limited Barian's Force!

00:17:58.511 --> 00:18:00.846
♪

00:18:00.846 --> 00:18:05.217
This card ranks up Utopia
into a Chaos Xyz Monster!

00:18:05.217 --> 00:18:09.121
I rebuild the Overlay
Network with Utopia!

00:18:09.121 --> 00:18:12.658
Go Chaos Xyz Evolution!

00:18:12.658 --> 00:18:15.261
♪

00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:20.866
Come on out Chaos Number 39:
Utopia Ray V!

00:18:20.866 --> 00:18:28.507
♪

00:18:28.507 --> 00:18:31.077
Utopia Ray V!

00:18:31.077 --> 00:18:34.814
Now I activate V Salamander's
special ability!

00:18:34.814 --> 00:18:38.684
I equip this monster
onto Utopia Ray V!

00:18:38.684 --> 00:18:40.353
Salamander Cloth!

00:18:40.353 --> 00:18:51.664
♪

00:18:51.664 --> 00:18:55.668
Next, I activate Utopia
Ray V's special ability!

00:18:55.668 --> 00:18:57.637
I use one
Chaos Overlay Unit

00:18:57.637 --> 00:18:59.872
to destroy one monster
on the field,

00:18:59.872 --> 00:19:02.908
and you take damage equal
to its attack points!

00:19:02.908 --> 00:19:05.077
♪

00:19:05.077 --> 00:19:06.412
Who cares.

00:19:06.412 --> 00:19:10.916
I have three monsters
on my field!

00:19:10.916 --> 00:19:14.854
Then I activate V Salamander's
other special ability.

00:19:14.854 --> 00:19:16.956
Now Utopia Ray V's
special ability

00:19:16.956 --> 00:19:20.359
affects every single monster
that's on your field!

00:19:20.359 --> 00:19:24.897
What? You mean...
all of them?

00:19:24.897 --> 00:19:29.301
Right! You have three monsters
with 2500 attack points each.

00:19:29.301 --> 00:19:33.539
That means you kiss 7500
life points bye-bye.

00:19:33.539 --> 00:19:35.775
Go, Utopia Ray V!

00:19:35.775 --> 00:19:40.146
V Salamander Inferno!

00:19:40.146 --> 00:19:42.048
No, I lost!

00:19:42.048 --> 00:19:52.058
♪

00:19:52.058 --> 00:19:55.428
Yeah! I am so
feelin' the flow!

00:19:55.428 --> 00:19:57.229
Yay!

00:19:57.229 --> 00:20:00.866
He was just purr-fect.

00:20:00.866 --> 00:20:02.902
(Astral)
V Salamander.

00:20:02.902 --> 00:20:07.940
Yuma never told me he had
another Barian card.

00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:09.475
So, Vector...

00:20:09.475 --> 00:20:12.545
Now you know not to mess
with Astral and me.

00:20:12.545 --> 00:20:22.254
♪

00:20:22.254 --> 00:20:24.457
(Ray) No!

00:20:24.457 --> 00:20:26.325
What are you doing?

00:20:26.325 --> 00:20:28.360
This is my fault.

00:20:28.360 --> 00:20:29.862
I'm sorry, Yuma!

00:20:29.862 --> 00:20:31.263
No, let him go!

00:20:31.263 --> 00:20:33.132
Yuma!

00:20:33.132 --> 00:20:36.869
I refuse to go away
empty handed, Yuma.

00:20:36.869 --> 00:20:40.639
I'd prefer you, but
your friend will do.

00:20:40.639 --> 00:20:42.775
Where are you taking him?

00:20:42.775 --> 00:20:46.412
♪

00:20:46.412 --> 00:20:49.415
The card will
give you a clue.

00:20:49.415 --> 00:20:50.149
♪

00:20:50.149 --> 00:20:52.618
Number 66.

00:20:52.618 --> 00:20:55.154
Wish your
friend luck, Yuma.

00:20:55.154 --> 00:20:56.489
He'll need it.

00:20:56.489 --> 00:20:59.358
-Save me, Yuma!
-Ray!

00:20:59.358 --> 00:21:01.060
RAY!

00:21:01.060 --> 00:21:08.601
♪

00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:10.236
(Yuma)
I'll find you, Ray!

00:21:10.236 --> 00:21:12.638
No matter what!

00:21:12.638 --> 00:21:14.874
Ray!

00:21:14.874 --> 00:21:20.379
♪

